# Typography & Text Layout Rules

## Font Declarations
- NEVER use `system-ui` font on macOS - it causes measurement inaccuracies
- Always use named fonts: Inter, Helvetica, Arial, etc.
- Font shorthand format: "16px Inter" or "500 18px Inter" (weight + size + family)
- Sync CSS font declarations with Pretext font strings exactly

## Line Height Standards
- Body text: 1.5 to 1.6
- Headings: 1.2 to 1.3
- Always specify line-height in pixels when using Pretext for calculations
- Example: 16px font = 24px line-height (1.5)

## Text Wrapping Defaults
- white-space: normal (or pre-wrap for textareas)
- word-break: normal
- overflow-wrap: break-word
- line-break: auto
- DO NOT use word-break: break-all

## Max Line Length
- Optimal: 65-75 characters for readability
- Max width: ~600px for body text at 16px

## Base Typography Scale
- Base: 16px
- Small: 14px
- Large: 18px
- H3: 20px
- H2: 24px
- H1: 32px

## Font Weights
- Regular: 400
- Medium: 500
- Bold: 600 or 700

## Implementation Notes
- Use Pretext's prepare() once per text block, not on every resize
- Call layout() on resize only - it's the fast path
- Cache prepared text when possible
- For dynamic content, recreate prepare() only when text actually changes

## Code Example
```typescript
import { prepare, layout } from '@chenglou/pretext'

// Do once:
const prepared = prepare(text, '16px Inter')

// Do on resize:
const { height, lineCount } = layout(prepared, containerWidth, 24)
```
